description.narrative: Analysis of the Education Management Information System (2019) data shows that the number of children in first Grade Primary with ECD experience increased both in percentage and nominal values. In 2018 about 44,665 Grade 1 children (64%) experienced ECD which increased to 48,454 children (65%) in 2019. Similarly, boys increased form 21,999 (63%) to 23,324 (65%) and girls from 23,066 (65%) in 2018 to 25,130 (65%). A review of the ECD policy was conducted in 2019 to ensure that it is cross-sectoral and reflects the SDG targets. Progressively more children are realizing their right to ECE. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/12/2019
